# Your rule content
- Make sure you follow SOLID principles
- Follow DRY principle- don't repeat yourself in code.
- Immutability. Don't change state implicitly.
- Especially single responsibility principle.
- Try not to write functions longer than 15 lines, if they get longer seperate them into smaller functions.
- Pay attention to encapsulation. 
- Always try to minimize the amount of direct dependencies between different code structures.
- don't use singleton. always prefer dependency inversion.
